\begin{lemma} \label{lem:uk-lc}
\runik is locally confluent.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
For simplicity, we directly prove that $\runi$ is locally confluent (\cref{lem:u-lc}).
The proof carries over to $\runik$ as the only required $\runi$-reductions under $ > k$
$\lambda$s are on \emph{labeled} subterms.
%it never requires $\runi$-reductions that are \emph{under} a $\lambda$-subterm.
\end{proof}

